2007-02-10 08:49:04 GMT	Ivan Shmakov <ivan@theory.asu.ru>	patch-5

    Summary:
      Improved option arguments handling in `hdfdump'.
    Revision:
      hdump-c--ivan--0.1--patch-5

    src/hdfdump.c (p-arg.h): Include it.
    (_, N_): Defined ``identity'' macros to simplify future i18n.
    (parse_opt): Reimplemented `-m', `-a' and `-s' options argument handling
    to use `p_arg_double' function, so garbage after a number leads to an
    error being reported; use `argp_error' instead of `error'; return
    `EINVAL' on error; improved error messages as well.
    
    src/Makefile.am (AM_CPPFLAGS, LDADD): New variables, facilitating use of
    the package library.

    modified files:
     src/Makefile.am src/hdfdump.c


